        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 2 at 12:09PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 1208 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Hoehne, or 8 miles north of Trinidad, moving east at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Trinidad, Model, and Hoehne.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
